Line-transect survey method from two NOAA research vessels. Transect lines followed a grid (established before each survey) to uniformly cover waters between the coast and approximately 556 km offshore. Surveys were designed with a uniform grid of transect lines anchored by a randomly chosen start point. Ships travelled at 16.7-18.5 km/h through the water.
